        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 6:16PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 616 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles east of Toston, or 18 miles southeast of Townsend, moving east
at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Ringling.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
